ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Are you a weirdo? Do you have a tendency to get stuck in your own brain? Are you bad at compartmentalizing your thoughts in the way professional life demands? Take it! It will be a breath of fresh air, as well as a continual challenge. If you're just looking to fill out your course schedule with a programmatic survey of Nietzsche, maybe look elsewhere.
I would recommend this to other grad students, especially those interested in continental philosophy, and have already done so.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I was taking this course out of department but it was more thought-provoking and in a sense more useful to me than the classes in my own department.
